2026-04-21 01:28:25 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['battery', 'power supply module indicator circuit wiring'] hypothesis_explanation='Diagnostics with all modules disconnected show 0 V across the battery terminals, meaning the inserted battery is discharged or faulty. Additionally, the internal wiring of the power supply indicator circuit is incorrect: the battery positive terminal is not connected to the PSU positive output cable, the PSU LED anode is floating, and the resistor negative side is unconnected. As a result, the power-supply LED cannot light, and no voltage is delivered to the downstream modules, so all control-module LEDs and the load lamp remain off.\n\nThe fault is therefore a combination of (1) a dead or missing 12 V source and (2) miswired indicator circuitry in the power-supply module. Repair consists of replacing the bad battery with a known-good 12 V battery and restoring correct wiring so that the battery positive connects to the PSU + output and to the LED/resistor network, the negative connects to PSU −, and the LED–resistor pair are correctly wired in parallel with the source.'
